# Volcano

Volcano is a serverless platform for building and deploying apps and AI agents.

This plugin exposes Volcano skills through `skills/`, which is a symlink to the canonical `sources/volcano-skills` submodule. It does not copy or fork the skill content.

Canonical sources:

- Plugin skills symlink: `plugins/cursor/skills -> ../../sources/volcano-skills`
- Local runtime install: `~/.volcano/AGENTS.md` and `~/.volcano/skills/*/SKILL.md`
- Source repository: `https://github.com/Kong/volcano-skills`
- Default web origin: `https://volcano.dev`

## Before any Volcano work

1. Check whether `~/.volcano/AGENTS.md` exists and is non-empty.
2. If it is missing, install/refresh the canonical instructions and skills with:

   ```sh
   curl -fsSL "https://volcano.dev/bootstrap.sh" -o /tmp/volcano-bootstrap.sh && sh /tmp/volcano-bootstrap.sh --apply --agent cursor
   ```

   For local Volcano web development, use the localhost origin explicitly:

   ```sh
   export VOLCANO_WEB_URL=http://localhost:3000 && curl -fsSL "http://localhost:3000/bootstrap.sh" -o /tmp/volcano-bootstrap.sh && sh /tmp/volcano-bootstrap.sh --apply --agent cursor
   ```

3. Read `~/.volcano/AGENTS.md` before taking Volcano actions.
4. Use the canonical plugin skills when relevant (`volcano-platform`, `volcano-sdk`, `volcano-functions`, etc.).
5. Prefer the `volcano` CLI for Volcano actions. Use `volcano <area> --help` and `--json` where useful.

## Safety

Follow the safety model in `~/.volcano/AGENTS.md`. In particular, production deploys, deletions, secret/variable changes, permission/visibility changes, custom domains, and billing/account changes require explicit user confirmation.
